com.bmd.jrt.channel

Interface OutputChannel<OUTPUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Channel, Iterable<OUTPUT>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IOChannel.IOChannelOutput<OUTPUT>

    public interface OutputChannel<OUTPUT>
extends Channel, Iterable<OUTPUT>
    Interface defining an output channel, that is the channel used to read the routine invocation output data.

    Note that the delivery order of the output data might not be guaranteed.

    Created by davide on 9/4/14.

      • afterMax

        @Nonnull
OutputChannel<OUTPUT> afterMax(@Nonnull
                                     TimeDuration timeout)
        Tells the channel to wait at max the specified time duration for the next result to be available.

        By default the timeout is set to a few seconds to avoid unexpected deadlocks.

        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum timeout.
        Returns:
        this channel.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified timeout is null.
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already bound to a consumer.
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted with an exception.

      • eventuallyDeadLock

        @Nonnull
OutputChannel<OUTPUT> eventuallyDeadLock(boolean throwException)
        Tells the channel to throw a ReadDeadLockException in case no result is available before the timeout has elapsed.

        By default no exception will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        throwException - whether to throw a deadlock exception.
        Returns:
        this channel.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already bound to a consumer.

        See Also:

      • readFirst

        OUTPUT readFirst()
        Reads the first available result by waiting at the maximum for the set timeout.
        Returns:
        the first available result.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already bound to a consumer.
        NoSuchElementException - if no output is available (it might be thrown also in the case the read timeout elapses and no deadlock exception is set to be thrown).
        ReadDeadLockException - if the channel is set to throw an exception when the timeout elapses.
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted with an exception.
        See Also:
        afterMax(com.bmd.jrt.time.TimeDuration), afterMax(long, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit), immediately(), eventuallyDeadLock(boolean)
